<link href="adcp.css" rel="stylesheet"><entry><xh5> there is no escape from something • there is no escaping something</xh5><p> <i>there is no escape from something—</i>1. said of a place from which one cannot get away: The jagged rocks are forbidding and dangerous. <u>There is no escape from</u> here. 2. said of a difficult situation that cannot be avoided or ignored: If <u>there is no escape</u> from check, it is checkmate and the game is over. </p><p><i>there is no escaping something</i>— = there is no escape from something 2: <u>There is no escaping</u> the fact that the government has become very unpopular.</p> </entry>
